metadata.name: Pixel Management #906
metadata.description:
#tezpole has demonstrated to us all the importance of effective Cable Management. Intrigued by this challenge, I've delved deep into the pixels of this issue. üôÇ

Drawing inspiration from Rev Dan Catt‚Äôs 'Tally!' and applying similar principles of Cable Management, I've assembled a fun and free OE project.

This project dynamically evolves with each iteration.Grid is determined by a random value calculated as follows: the lower bound starts at 3 and increases incrementally with every 100 iterations, while the upper bound starts at 4 and increases with every 30 iterations. In practical terms, as the iteration count increases, both the minimum and maximum possible number of cols&rows gradually increase.

3200x3200px
Press [s] for .jpeg | Press [p] for .png
Made with p5.js

Rob Scalera | 2023

metadata.name: Edge #5
metadata.description: This collaboration was destined to happen. The joint effort of two landscape enthusiasts, each with a distinct approach to creation and style, resulted in something new for both. 'Edge' is a project showcasing subtle lines that connect in the subconscious something not opposing but slightly different. It's the edge that separates the dusty country road you're driving on from the beautiful, colorful landscape outside the car window. It's the edge that almost imperceptibly divides day and night during sunrises and sunsets. It's the edge where AI and generative art have converged...

metadata.name: V.Mountains #68
metadata.description:
V.Mountains is an abstract representation of the turbulence and chaos of our life.



The mountain is a symbol of the way that life is constantly in flux,

of the way that we are constantly trying to make sense of the world around us.



The mountain is a source of inspiration, a place of refuge, a source of strength.

It is a place where we can go to reflect on our lives, to find peace and solace.



The mountain is a symbol of hope.

It is a reminder that, no matter how dark and cold the world may be, there is always a chance for new beginnings.



The mountain is a symbol of the human spirit, and of our ability to persevere in the face of adversity.

It is a representation of our journey through life, with all of its ups and downs.

It is a reminder that, no matter how difficult the path may be,
we can always reach the summit if we are willing to put in the hard work.



Created in Vanilla Javascript.


S - to download image.


Libraries used:

noise.js by Joseph Gentle.
Javascript-Voronoi by Raymond Hill.

metadata.name: September #361
metadata.description:
The Summer Ends
---------------
Controls:
S or double tap (mobile): Download image

A: Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)

1-6: Modify scale (1 = default, 1500 x 2000px, 6 = maximum, 9000 x 12000px (performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F: Fit to current screen size

T: Toggle grain and texture overlay
H: Toggle shape outlines

B: Cycle border sizes (0 -> 50 -> 75 -> 100 -> 150px)
C: Cycle border colors

I: Cycle visible layers

L: Toggle ‚Äúlive mode‚Äù. This mode will continuously redraw a new output every few seconds using the same base parameters as the original output, but with slight variations.

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)
---------------

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #586
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.
